[Rosa Brett](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rosa_Brett) was John (the
painter's) older sister.  The ODNB has "Brett, Rosa [pseud. Rosarius]
(1829–1882), painter, was born on 7 December 1829 and baptized at St George's,
Camberwell, Surrey, on 26 March 1830, the eldest of the five children of
Captain Charles Curtis Brett (1789–1865), veterinary surgeon in the 12th
lancers, and his wife, Ann, née Pilbean (b. 1808/9), of Tonbridge, Kent."

> His father, Charles Curtis Brett, had a background in both the army and the
> navy. He served as a midshipman on HMS Egmont, a 74-gun warship, between 1816
> and 1823. In 1833, he joined the Twelfth Lancers, an army regiment, as a
> veterinary surgeon, and he continued to work in the army until his retirement
> in 1860.

